### Logo Rules (all brands)

- Minimum clear space: half the height of the logo on all sides.
- Never rotate, skew, add shadows, or place on busy backgrounds.
- On dark backgrounds: use the dark-variant lockup (lighter primary stroke + near-white wordmark).
- On light backgrounds: use the light-variant lockup (full primary stroke + slate-night or product-ink wordmark).
- Never use gradients in the canonical SVG file. Marketing surfaces add ambient effects in CSS.
- Never recolor the accent. Each product's accent is locked per the table above.
- Never put the paperclip mark on a product page — it's parent-brand only. Each product uses its own glyph.

