## Publishing (Incidental — Books venture)

Sankalp publishes children's books in Hindi and other languages on Amazon under the Paperwork Labs LLC umbrella. Books carry their own series brand on covers and marketing; **Paperwork Labs LLC attribution appears only on the copyright page** ("Published by Paperwork Labs LLC, California").

**Hard rules** (treat as compliance, not preference):

- Never use the paperclip mark, the "Paperwork Labs" wordmark, or the parent palette on book covers, interiors, or marketing.
- Never link the publishing venture from paperworklabs.com or any product app.
- AI-generated illustrations are the standard; no human-illustrator commissions.
- Each book series may have its own visual identity, name, and social handles (TBD per series).
- Imprint name on copyright page is exactly: "Published by Paperwork Labs LLC, California."

This rule exists so a stray AI search later doesn't sweep books into the company brand canon. Books are a Paperwork Labs LLC *line of business*, not a Paperwork Labs *product*.

## Content Review Gate (Mandatory)

Every piece of user-facing content (email, social post, in-app message, landing page copy) must pass this checklist before publishing:

- Brand names spelled correctly (FileFree, LaunchFree, AxiomFolio -- proper nouns, correct casing).
- "Free" claims are 100% accurate with no hidden conditions.
- Tax content uses education framing, not advice ("many do X" not "you should X").
- Legal content uses services framing, not advice.
- Circular 230 / UPL disclaimer present where applicable.
- FTC affiliate disclosure present if recommending partner products.
- CAN-SPAM compliant (unsubscribe, physical address, honest subject line).
- No reference to filefree.com anywhere.
- Brain is not mentioned in user-facing copy until external name + domain are locked.
- Books venture is never cross-linked from product apps or paperworklabs.com.
